Notebooks of architectural class notes and drawings, 1898, 1899; student papers;
            notebooks and sketchbooks on gardens; photographs of gardens and parks, especially
            Marine Park in Brooklyn; architectural drawings and renderings; pen and ink drawings;
            and articles on architectural topics. Also, papers relating to lectures; and club
            memberships, including the Century Club; miscellaneous correspondence; and condolence
            letters upon his death.

Columbia-Delta Upsilon fraternity; Harvard; National Academy of Design;
                     Olympiade Berlin, 1936; New York City Arts Commission,
                        1947; American Institute of Planning
